Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English (Kent): variant of   Brookman  , a topographic name for someone who lived by a brook or stream (see   Brook   1).","Americanized form of Jewish (from Poland) <b>Brokman</b>: occupational name, an agent form based on the Yiddish verb <i>brokn</i> ‘to crumble, shred’.","Americanized form of German   Brockmann  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Brookman","meanings":["English: topographic name from Middle English <i>brokman</i> ‘dweller by the brook’. Compare   Brooker   and   Brookins  .","Americanized form of German <b>Bruckmann</b> or <b>Brückmann</b> (see   Bruckman  ).","Americanized form of Dutch <b>Broekman</b>: topographic name for someone living by a <i>broek</i> ‘swampy field, marsh’."]},{"name":"Brockmann","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  German Ernst, Heinrich, Juergen, Kurt, Siegfried, Uwe, Wilhelm.","North German: topographic name for someone who lived by a marsh, from Middle Low German <i>brook</i> ‘bog, swamp’ + <i>man</i> ‘man’.","Jewish: variant of   Brockman  ."]}]},{"name":"Margaret","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["An extremely common given name from the Middle Ages onwards, derived via Old French <i>Marguerite</i> and Latin <i>Margarita</i> from Greek <i>Margarītēs</i>, from <i>margaron</i> ‘pearl’, a word ultimately of Hebrew origin. The name was always understood to mean ‘pearl’ throughout the Middle Ages. The first  St Margaret  was martyred at Antioch in Pisidia during the persecution instigated by the  Emperor Diocletian  in the early 4th century. However, there is some doubt about her name, as the same saint is venerated in the Orthodox Church as   Marina .  There were several other saintly bearers of the name, including St Margaret of Scotland (  d. 1093 ), wife of  King Malcolm Canmore  and daughter of Edmund Ironside of England. It was also the name of the wife of  Henry VI  of England,  Margaret of Anjou  (  1430–82 ), and of  Margaret Tudor  (  1489–1541 ), sister of  Henry VIII , who married James IV of Scotland and ruled as regent there after his death.  See also  Margery  ,   Marjorie ."],"variants":[{"name":"Margareta","meanings":["From the Latin form of Greek <i>Margarītēs</i>.  See  <b>Margaret</b>   ."]},{"name":"Margaretta","meanings":["Formed from Margaret."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"When Lady Margaret Brockman was born in 1440, in Hestercombe, Somerset, England, United Kingdom, her father, Sir Henry Brockman, was 18 and her mother, Lady Rebecca Anne Chilton, was 14. She married John Warre in 1465, in Somerset, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 2 sons. She died in 1465, in Somerset, England, United Kingdom, at the age of 25."},"et":{"1440–1465":"1440–1465","1435–1500":"1435–1500","1440–1502":"1440–1502","1460–1512":"1460–1512","1467–1541":"1467–1541","1475–1525":"1475–1525","1422–1473":"1422–1473","1426–1445":"1426–1445","Aft 1445":"pärast 1445","1440":"1440","1473":"1473","1460":"1460","1426":"1426","1525":"1525","1502":"1502","1512":"1512","1435":"1435","1445":"1445","1467":"1467","1500":"1500","1422":"1422","1465":"1465","1475":"1475","1541":"1541","1439":"1439","Kent, England, United Kingdom":"Kent, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Folkestone, Kent, England":"Folkestone, Kent, England","Hestercombe, Somerset, England, United Kingdom":"Hestercombe, Somerset, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Somerset, England, United Kingdom":"Somerset, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1440–1465":"1440–1465","1435–1500":"1435–1500","1440–1502":"1440–1502","1460–1512":"1460–1512","1467–1541":"1467–1541","1475–1525":"1475–1525","1422–1473":"1422–1473","1426–1445":"1426–1445","Aft 1445":"1445 jälkeen","1440":"1440","1473":"1473","1460":"1460","1426":"1426","1525":"1525","1502":"1502","1512":"1512","1435":"1435","1445":"1445","1467":"1467","1500":"1500","1422":"1422","1465":"1465","1475":"1475","1541":"1541","1439":"1439","Kent, England, United 